cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.FM 

The paper presents a data structure for formalizing the behaviors of recursive programs that interact with their environment, and studies the compositional properties of interpreters built from event handlers. This suggests a focus on programming languages and semantics (cs.PL), as well as software engineering (cs.SE) and formal methods (cs.FM). The use of coinductive types and weak bisimulation suggests a connection to logic (cs.LO), while the application to compiler correctness suggests a connection to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
